{title: Ebony Eyes}
{artist: The Everly Brothers}
{composer: written by John D. Loudermilk}

[C]On a weekend pass I wouldn't have had time
To [G7]get home and marry that baby of mine
So I [C]went to the chaplain and [F]he authorized
Me to [C]send for my [G7]ebony [C]eyes
My [F]ebony eyes was [C]coming to me
From [F]out of the skies on [C]flight twelve o [G7]three
